lass=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Jan 03, 2023</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104pav1665702692575.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/pav1665702692575.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/pav1665702692575.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"pav1665702692575\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"pav1665702692575__uinstopr_405143\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Return the handle to an operation.</p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"pav1665702692575__topic_d121589e1_d121590e1_d121591e1\">\n<div class=\"p\">\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104pav1665702692575_html_0\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"pav1665702692575__codeblock_qfs_z5c_bwb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\"><code class=\"ph codeph language-plaintext\">long uinstopr (UHACT</code> hInst, <code class=\"ph codeph language-plaintext\">UCHAR*</code> oprName, <code class=\"ph codeph language-plaintext\">int</code> reserved, <code class=\"ph codeph language-plaintext\">UHACT*</code> phOpr<code class=\"ph codeph language-plaintext\">);</code></code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"pav1665702692575__topic_d86252e1_d86253e1_d86254e1_d86255e1_d86256e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d145988e74\">Parameters</h2>\n<dl class=\"dl parml\" id=\"pav1665702692575__parml_kpj_m5c_bwb\">\n<dt class=\"dt pt dlterm\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">hInst</var></dt>\n<dd class=\"dd pd\">The instance handle as returned by <code class=\"ph codeph\">unewinst</code></dd>\n<dt class=\"dt pt dlterm\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">oprName</var></dt>\n<dd class=\"dd pd\">The name of the operation to instantiate</dd>\n<dt class=\"dt pt dlterm\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">reserved</var></dt>\n<dd class=\"dd pd\">This parameter is reserved for future use and is currently not used. We recommend\n                  you supply zero.</dd>\n<dt class=\"dt pt dlterm\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">phOpr</var></dt>\n<dd class=\"dd pd\">(Output) The operation handle</dd>\n</dl>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"pav1665702692575__topic_d86257e1_d86258e1_d86259e1_d86260e1_d86261e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d145988e125\">Return Values</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"pav1665702692575__d5955e20\">For more information, see the \"Call-In API Return\n        Codes\" topic.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"pav1665702692575__topic_d86262e1_d86263e1_d86264e1_d86265e1_d86266e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d145988e134\">Use</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"pav1665702692575__d5956e20\">Library:  <span class=\"ph filepath\">ucall</span></p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"pav1665702692575__topic_d86267e1_d86268e1_d86269e1_d86270e1_d86271e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d145988e146\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"pav1665702692575__p_d121625e1_d121626e1_d121627e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">uinstopr</code> returns the handle of the\n            specified operation in an existing component instance. The handle is returned in the\n            parameter <var class=\"keyword varname\">phOpr</var>. The operation handle can subsequently be used to get\n            or set parameters, and to activate the operation using <code class=\"ph codeph\">uopract</code>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"pav1665702692575__p_d121628e1_d121629e1_d121630e1\">Note that there is no function to delete an\n            operation. However, you do need to delete the operation handle after use by calling\n               <code class=\"ph codeph\">ufreeh</code>.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"pav1665702692575__section_l4n_s5c_bwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d145988e169\">Example: uecreate, uedelete, ufreeh, uinstdel, uinstnew, uinstopr, and\n            uopract</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">The following simple call-in program shows how to activate the EXEC\n            operation of the service MYSVC. As usual, error checking has been omitted for the sake\n            of brevity.</p>\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104pav1665702692575_html_1\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"pav1665702692575__codeblock_np4_v5c_bwb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">#include &lt;h3gl.h&gt;\n\nvoid main (void)\n{\nUHACT hEnv; /* Uniface environment */\nUHACT hIn; /* Instance handle */\nUHACT hOp; /* Operation handle */\nlong opStat; /* Activate status return parameter */\n\n/* Create the environment */\nuecreate(1, 0, 0, \"my.asn\", 0, 0, &amp;hEnv);\n/* Instantiate service MYSVC */\nuinstnew(hEnv, \"MYSVC\", 0, 0, UDEFAULT_COMM_MODE, 0, &amp;hIn, 0);\n\nuinstopr(hIn, \"EXEC\", 0, &amp;hOp); /* Instantiate the EXEC operation */\nuopract (hOp, &amp;opStat, 0); /* Activate the operation */\nuinstdel(hIn, 0); /* Destroy the instance */\n\nufreeh (&amp;hOp); /* Free the operation */\nufreeh (&amp;hIn); /* Free the instance */\nuedelete(hEnv, -1); /* Shut down the environment */\nufreeh (&amp;hEnv); /* Free the environment handle */\nreturn 0; // on success\t\t\t\t\n}</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jhh1665702691902.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Call-In API Return Codes</a><p>Codes that can possibly be returned by functions from the 3GL call-in API are consistent with the values returned by the ProcScript function $procerror, unless noted otherwise.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2530850\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2530850\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "uinstopr Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Jan 03, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Return the handle to an operation. Explain this code long uinstopr (UHACT hInst, UCHAR* oprName, int reserved, UHACT* phOpr ); Copy Parameters hInst The instance handle as returned by unewinst oprName The name of the operation to instantiate reserved This parameter is reserved for future use and is currently not used. We recommend you supply zero. phOpr (Output) The operation handle Return Values For more information, see the \"Call-In API Return Codes\" topic. Use Library: ucall Description uinstopr returns the handle of the specified operation in an existing component instance. The handle is returned in the parameter phOpr . The operation handle can subsequently be used to get or set parameters, and to activate the operation using uopract . Note that there is no function to delete an operation. However, you do need to delete the operation handle after use by calling ufreeh . Example: uecreate, uedelete, ufreeh, uinstdel, uinstnew, uinstopr, and uopract The following simple call-in program shows how to activate the EXEC operation of the service MYSVC. As usual, error checking has been omitted for the sake of brevity. Explain this code #include <h3gl.h> void main (void) { UHACT hEnv; /* Uniface environment */ UHACT hIn; /* Instance handle */ UHACT hOp; /* Operation handle */ long opStat; /* Activate status return parameter */ /* Create the environment */ uecreate(1, 0, 0, \"my.asn\", 0, 0, &hEnv); /* Instantiate service MYSVC */ uinstnew(hEnv, \"MYSVC\", 0, 0, UDEFAULT_COMM_MODE, 0, &hIn, 0); uinstopr(hIn, \"EXEC\", 0, &hOp); /* Instantiate the EXEC operation */ uopract (hOp, &opStat, 0); /* Activate the operation */ uinstdel(hIn, 0); /* Destroy the instance */ ufreeh (&hOp); /* Free the operation */ ufreeh (&hIn); /* Free the instance */ uedelete(hEnv, -1); /* Shut down the environment */ ufreeh (&hEnv); /* Free the environment handle */ return 0; // on success } Copy Related Links Call-In API Return Codes Codes that can possibly be returned by functions from the 3GL call-in API are consistent with the values returned by the ProcScript function $procerror, unless noted otherwise. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}